r files case under [[Section 377 of the Indian Penal Code|Section 377]] against Lila's partner Tarulata who underwent FTM sex change to marry Lila Chavda in 1989 (Apr)<ref>[http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/case-of-a-curious-marriage-in-gujarat/1/315005.html \"Gender jam \u2013 Case of a curious marriage in Gujarat\"], ''India Today'', April 15, 1990.</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United States}} ''[[Shamakami]]'' newsletter for South Asian lesbian and bi women comes out (Jun)<ref name=\"Orinam_Magazines_and_Journals\" /><ref>Nayan Shah, \"Sexuality, Identity, and the Uses in History\"], in David L. Eng, Alice Y. Hom (eds), ''Q & A: Queer in Asian America''.</ref>\n* {{flagicon|India}} India's first gay magazine, ''[[Bombay Dost]]'', founded by [[Ashok Row Kavi]] (Jun)<ref name=\"Orinam_Magazines_and_Journals\" />\n* {{flagicon|India}} Freedom newsletter published in Gulbarga (Sep)<ref name=\"Orinam_Magazines_and_Journals\" />\n* {{flagicon|India}} Fun Club starts in Calcutta to organize social gatherings (Dec)<ref>[http://www.digitalcultureandeducation.com/cms/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/theHIVe_3006.pdf Digital Culture And Education The HIVe Volume 4, Issue 1, 2012]</ref><ref>[http://www.unipune.ac.in/snc/cssh/HumanRights/07%20STATE%20AND%20GENDER/20.pdf ''Humjinsi: A Resource Book on Lesbian, Gay, and Bisexual Rights in India''], p. 102.</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Canada}} Desh Pardesh (1990 - 2001, multidisciplinary queer South Asian arts festival in Toronto, ON). See citation for oral history project about the festival.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.savac.net/collection/desh-pardesh/ |title = Desh Pardesh}}</ref><ref>http://www.rungh.org/issues/Rungh_v1_n1-2.pdf</ref>\n* Vandana Cibbal and Simmi Kapoor RIP<ref name=\"Bacchetta_Rescaling\" />\n* Films:\n** ''Jareena: Portrait of a Hijra'' by Prem Kalliat<ref>[http://www.twn.org/catalog/pages/cpage.aspx?rec=1129&card=price Third World Newsreel]</ref>\n** ''Flesh and Paper'' by [[Pratibha Parmar]] about Suniti Namjoshi<ref>[htt