\"PoliticsFemaleBody\">Ketu Katrak, [https://books.google.com/books?id=IEE1529dS1IC&pg=PA198&lpg=PA198&dq=Aarambh+magazine+%22new+delhi%22+gay&source=bl&hl=en ''The Politics of the Female Body: Postcolonial Women Writers'']</ref> (need better reference)\n* {{flagicon|United States}} Trikone Atlanta born<ref name=\"NQAPIA_Queer_Asian_Compass\" />\n* {{flagicon|India}} Naz and Sakhi Seminar on Alternative Sexualities in New Delhi<ref>Janaki Nair, Mary E. John (eds), [https://books.google.com/books?id=gUJ6112aGZQC&pg=PA39&lpg=PA39&dq=Naz+and+Sakhi+Seminar+on+Alternative+Sexualities+in+New+Delhi&source=bl&hl=en ''A Question of Silence: The Sexual Economies of Modern India''], p. 39.</ref>\n* {{flagicon|India}} Samraksha AIDS organization formed in Bangalore (Dec)<ref>{{cite web|title=Samraksha: About Us|url=http://www.samraksha.org/html/about_us.html|accessdate=22 June 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Epidemic_of_Abuse\">{{cite journal|last1=Csete|first1=Joanne|title=India: Epidemic of Abuse: Police Harassment of HIV/AIDS Outreach Workers in India|journal=Human Rights Watch India|date=July 2002|volume=14|issue=5|page=14|url=https://www.hrw.org/reports/2002/india2/india0602.pdf|accessdate=22 June 2014}}</ref>\n* Modern-day traditional wedding Aditya Advani and Michael Tarr performed by Swami Bodhananda<ref name=\"Vanita_Love's_Rite\">{{cite book|last1=Vanita|first1=Ruth|title=Love's Rite: Same-Sex Marriage in India and the West|date=October 2005|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|isbn=978-1403981608|page=234|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ofDIAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA234&lpg=PA234&dq=Aditya+Advani+and+Michael+Tarr|accessdate=22 June 2014}}</ref>\n* Books:\n** ''Queer Looks'' edited by Pratibha Parmar, John Greyson, Martha Gever.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Parmar|first1=Pratibha|last2=Greyson|first2=John|last3=Gever|first3=Martha|title=Queer Looks|date=Sep 1993|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0415907422|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/queerlooksperspe0000unse}}</ref>\n** ''Femini