ar and others<ref name=\"Mobile\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Description|url=https://groups.yahoo.com/neo/groups/Sagrrls/info|website=SAGrrls|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United States}} Pride Utsav hosted by Trikone in San Francisco (Jun)(parent of DesiQ)<ref>{{cite web|title=Trikone Presents|url=http://www.qrd.org/qrd/orgs/TRIKONE/pride_utsav95|website=QRD|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ness|first1=Carol|title=Prying open closets of South Asian gays|url=http://www.sfgate.com/news/article/Prying-open-closets-of-South-Asian-gays-3146401.php|website=SF Gate|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United States}} Trikone's website debuts \u2013 the first ever for a South Asian LGBT group<ref name=Mobile />\n* {{flagicon|Canada}} Activist Kalpesh Oza, AIDS researcher and Desh Pradesh artist/organizer, passes away in Toronto (Jun)<ref name=desiq-2006-timeline /><ref>{{cite web|title=New Investigator Awards|url=http://www.cahr-acrv.ca/content/uploads/2012/07/CAHR-2011-Conference-Program.pdf|website=cahr-acrv.ca/content/uploads/2012/07/CAHR-2011-Conference-Program.pdf|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Inventory of the Desh Pardesh fonds|url=http://archivesfa.library.yorku.ca/filelist/2007-042.522.htm|website=Clara Thomas Archives|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=2 Idiots Gujurati Drama Staged in Toronto|url=http://www.weeklyvoice.com/community-news/2-idiots-gujarati-drama-staged-toronto/|website=Weekly Voice|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Canada}} ''Awaz-e-Atish: Voice of Fire'' publication by Atish Network Society (1995-1996)<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.clga.ca/periodicals/a|website = Canadian Gay Lesbian Archives|accessdate = 21 July 2015|title = Periodicals (LGBT): A}}</ref>\n* Sulaiman Mohammed, founding member of Atish passes away (Aug)<ref name=desiq-2006-timeline /><!--inquiry out to Vancouver LGBT community for references-->\n* South Asia lesbians and bisexual