leindia.com/life/1557-here-comes-the-bride-and-the-bride.html|accessdate=11 October 2015}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United States}} [[Al-Fatiha Foundation]], LGBT Muslim conference (US)<ref name=desiq-2013-timeline />\n* {{flagicon|India}} LGBT India conducts Operation Sparsh to educate political parties on sexual minority rights<ref name=desiq-2013-timeline />\n* {{flagicon|United States}} \"Gay Desi SF Bay\" mailing list for San Francisco Bay Area queer desis started by Rakesh Modi<ref name=desiq-2013-timeline />\n* Books:\n** {{flagicon|India}} ''Same Sex Love in India'' \u2013 Readings from Literature and History by [[Ruth Vanita]] and [[Saleem Kidwai]]<ref>{{Cite book|title = Same-sex Love in India: Readings from Literature and History|url = https://books.google.com/books?id=_UKmQgAACAAJ&dq=031222169X|publisher = St. Martin's Press|date = 2000|access-date = 2015-04-03|isbn = 9780312221690|first = Ruth|last = Vanita|first2 = Saleem|last2 = Kidwai}}</ref>\n** {{flagicon|India}} ''Humjinsi'', a resource book for LGB rights published (India). Also includes papers presented at a seminar in Mumbai (1997)<ref name=\"desiq-2013-timeline\" />\n* Films:\n** ''Bombay Eunuchs'', directors Alexandra Shiva, Sean McDonald and Michelle Gucovsky<ref name=\"desiq-2006-timeline\" />\n\n'''2001'''\n* {{flagicon|Nepal}} [[Blue Diamond Society]], Nepal's only organization for sexual minorities founded<ref>{{Cite web|title = Blue Diamond Society: About us|url = http://www.bds.org.np/about-us/|website = Blue Diamond Society|accessdate = 2015-05-10}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|India}} Lakshyaa \u2013 first Gujarati gay magazine comes out<ref>{{cite web|title=Magazines and Journals|url=http://orinam.net/resources-for/lgbt/magazines-and-journals/|website=Orinam|accessdate=22 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Menon|first1=Lekha|title=I am proud, I am gay|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/ahmedabad-times/I-am-proud-I-am-gay/articleshow/1249531931.cms|accessdate=22 December 2015|date=Dec