range Obsession|date=Dec 1992|publisher=Penguin|location=India|isbn=978-0140178333|edition=1st}}</ref><ref name=GLBTQ_SA_Literature>{{cite web|last1=Nelson|first1=Emmanuel|title=South Asian Literature|url=http://www.glbtq.com/literature/south_asian_lit.html|website=GLBTQ.com|accessdate=22 June 2014}}</ref>\n*Play: ''Draupadi\u2019s Robes'' by Raminder Kaur, starring Parminder Sekhon and Poulomi Desai. The production included poetry, music and dance with performers from London's Asian LGBTTQI communities<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sohayavisions.com/chandica-arts|title=CHANDICA ARTS {{!}} Sohaya Visions|website=silentsisters|language=en|access-date=2019-08-29}}</ref>\n\n'''1994'''\n* {{flagicon|India}} ''Vadamalli'' by novelist Su.Samuthiram is the first Tamil novel about Aravaani community in Tamil Nadu<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/making-queer-history-it-should-matter-we-existed-and-fought-46742|title=The Making of Queer History: It should matter that we existed, and fought|last=Moulee|date=2016-07-16|access-date=2019-07-10}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|India}} G.A.Y (Good as You) group formed in Bangalore<ref>{{cite book|author1=Chandra Balachandran|editor1-last=Srivastava|editor1-first=Sanjay|title=Sexual Sites, Seminal Attitudes: Sexualities, Masculinities and Culture in South Asia|date=2004|publisher=Sage|isbn=978-0761997771|page=176|edition=Issue 4|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sOcd93lMhR0C&pg=PA176&lpg=PA176&dq=%22Good+As+You%22+Bangalore+history&source=bl&hl=en|accessdate=22 June 2014|chapter=Emerging Gay Geographies}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United States}} ''[[Time Magazine|TIME]]'' names [[Urvashi Vaid]] one of the top leaders under 40<ref>{{cite web|title=Urvashi Vaid|url=http://lgbthistorymonth.com/urvashi-vaid?tab=biography|website=LGBT History Month|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|India}} Humsafar Trust registered in India<ref>{{cite web|title=Humsafar Trust: About Us|url=http://www.humsafar.org/about.