ade]], but protested along with Sakhi, a women's organization.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mohin|first1=Andrea|title=South Asian Gay and Lesbian Group Marches for India|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1994/08/22/nyregion/south-asian-gay-and-lesbian-group-marches-for-india.html|accessdate=23 June 2014|newspaper=The New York Times|date=August 22, 1994}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sengupta|first1=Somini|title=Gay South Asians Sidelined at Parades|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/08/04/nyregion/gay-south-asians-sidelined-at-parades.html|accessdate=23 June 2014|newspaper=The New York Times|date=August 6, 1996}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title = The Karma of Brown Folk|last = Prashad|first = Vijay|year = |isbn = |location = |pages = 117}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Shah|first1=Purvi|editor1-last=Shah|editor1-first=Sonia|title=Dragon Ladies: Asian American Feminists Breathe Fire|chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/dragonladies00soni|chapter-url-access=registration|date=1997|publisher=South End Press|chapter=Activist Exclusion at the India Day Parade}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United States}} MASALA formed in Boston<ref>{{cite book|last1=Das Gupta|first1=Monisha|title=Unruly Immigrants: Rights, Activism, and Transnational South Asian Politics in the United States|date=2006|publisher=Duke University Publisher|isbn=978-0822388173|page=167|url=https://books.google.com/?id=e1nSfsMRkFcC&pg=PA196&lpg=PA196&dq=MASALA+formed+in+Boston+gay|accessdate=23 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Parayath|first1=Chitra|title=MASALA Mela In Boston|url=http://www.lokvani.com/lokvani/article.php?article_id=2025|publisher=Lokvani|accessdate=23 June 2014|date=2004-09-30}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|India}} Vimla Farooqui of National Federation of Indian Women asks PM to stop gay meet claiming homosexuality is Western<ref name=\"Joseph_Social_Work_Practice\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=GAY FILM FESTIVAL OPPOSED IN INDIA|url=http://listserv.indianetwork.org/cgi/wa.cgi?A2=ind9411A&L=INDIA-D&F=&S=&P=9860|website=listser