ita Dasgupta|author3=Pallav Patankar|author4=Minati Sinha|title=A People Stronger: The Collectivization of MSM and TG groups in India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Tp2HAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA137|date=24 January 2013|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=978-81-321-1142-9|page=137}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United States}} First International Retreat of LGBT Muslims in Boston (Oct)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaytoday.com/garchive/world/111098wo.htm|title=Muslim Homosexuals Host 1st International Retreat in Boston|last=|first=|date=1998|website=GayToday.com|accessdate=21 July 2015}}</ref>\n* DESIDYKES created<ref name=desiq-2013-timeline /><ref>{{cite web|title=Yahoo Groups|url=https://groups.yahoo.com/neo/groups/desidykes/info|website=DesiDykes|accessdate=11 August 2015}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|India}} Gay Bombay (internet group) formed<ref>{{cite web|title=Gay Bombay|url=http://gaybombay.org/about-2/about-gb-1|website=Gay Bombay|accessdate=11 August 2015}}</ref><ref name=Gay_Bombay>{{cite book|last1=Shahani|first1=Parmesh|title=Gay Bombay: Globalization, Love and (Be)longing in Contemporary India|date=2008|publisher=SAGE Publications India|isbn=978-8132100140|page=85|url=https://books.google.com/?id=woaHAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA85&lpg=PA85&dq=%22gay+bombay%22+mailing+list+founded#v=onepage&q=%22gay%20bombay%22%20mailing%20list%20founded&f=false|accessdate=11 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Gay Bombay Mailing List|url=http://gborg1.tripod.com/interact/maillist.html|website=Tripod|accessdate=11 August 2015}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|India}} GHAR (Gay Housing Assistance Resource) mailing lists start, eventually covering Mumbai, Kolkata, Chennai, Delhi, Bangalore, Canada, and the United States<ref>{{Cite web|title = Sachin Jain has started an initiative...|url = https://www.facebook.com/gaylove.smile/posts/352525768162245|website = Facebook|accessdate = 2015-08-31|date = August 25, 2012}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Canada}} \"Funkasia\" South Asian club and cultural night started in [[Toronto|T