ins the primary source -->\n* {{flagicon|India}} Milan Project (Naz India) files case with National Human Rights Commission against psychiatric abuse of a homosexual patient subjected to aversion therapy (May)<ref name=desiq-2006-timeline /><ref name=Sexuality_Policy />\n* {{flagicon|United States}} [[Trikone]] magazine wins South Asian Journalists Association award for \"South Asian Queers Out on the Internet\" article(Jun)<ref>{{cite news|title=SAJA Announces 2001 Journalism Award Winners|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/saja-announces-2001-journalism-award-winners-fareed-zakaria-of-newsweek-to-receive-saja-journalism-leader-award-at-national-convention-of-south-asian-journalists-72175212.html|accessdate=22 December 2015|publisher=PRWire|date=June 14, 2001}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Columbia Alumnus Wins Student Prize from the South Asian Journalists Association|url=http://www.columbia.edu/cu/news/01/06/saja_2001_winners.html|website=Columbia News|accessdate=22 December 2015}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|India}} Four activists of Naz Foundation International arrested in Lucknow under [[Section 377 of the Indian Penal Code|Section 377]] in \"gay area,\" Naz and Bharosa offices raided (Jul)<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rajalakshmi|first1=TK|title=Targeting NGOs|url=http://www.frontline.in/static/html/fl1818/18181130.htm|accessdate=22 December 2015|agency=India Times|issue=Volume 18 \u2013 Issue 18|date=Sep 1\u201314, 2001}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Narrain|first1=Arvind|title=The Articulation of Queer Rights: The Emerging Right to Sexual Orientation and Gender Identity|url=http://altlawforum.org/publications/the-articulation-of-queer-rights-the-emerging-right-to-sexual-orientation-and-gender-identity/|website=Alternative Law Forum|accessdate=22 December 2015}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United States}} QFilmistan \u2013 first Queer South Asian film festival<ref>{{cite web|last1=Morris|first1=Gary|title=QFilmistan: The First South Asian LGBT Film Festival (September 2001)|u